    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Gwendolyn was embraced by her boyfriend days after his embrace, he was a son of a local steel magnate and thought the owned the town, he had certainly bought Gwendolyn when her family came through on the circus the year before, he got her jewels, furs, and other lavish presents, and only demanded the most debased, debauched, lecherous access to her body that she had ever experienced.  Her family had been of good Methodist stock, despite being carnies, and so Gwendolyn was overwhelmed by him and his demands, as well as the gifts.  She rapidly fell into a belief that what he did to her was normal and she should be quiet and take it, after all she was just another woman.  She snapped when she was embraced, and ate her sire that very night, she stood over his rapidly rotting remains and felt very good about herself.  Then the sheriff caught her, she was taken in and interrogated, she was given clemency as the prince had a thing for a pretty gal.  She was taught what was what and how to behave, and then put in exactly the same situation that she had been in with Franklin, with the addition of torture and feeding now.  Some three years later you killed him one night after he came home from attending a council meeting and started beating  you without talking or ranting as normal.  You lost it and tore into him, the firts time ever fighting back.  You left town that night and spent a frantic year on the road, traveling looking for a new home, a new situation of stabillity. You found the circus in Denver, they had a rather talented acrobat family in the big top, but you could do better, and you sought out the acrobats later and challenged to show them, they accepted and you have been part of the circus since.  You met Barouqe and he quickly took you under his wing and into his bed, unlike the prince he never tortures you and sometimes even says things that make you feel good like, \"you look pretty with your hair up like that\" or \"no other woman can handle me like you can\" even \"sometimes I wonder if you were sent by god or the devil, either way, whoever sent you to me sure did me a great deed\".  You know that Barouqe will replace Calabris in the Trinity and you will reside by him for all time, a place of honor at his feet."
        ],
        [
          "Derangements:"
        ],
        [
          "1. You always have to have a domitor, your broken, you cant make the big decisions in your life, you love them and will do anything for them no matter how bad they are to you.  (mechanically, you will do this unless they spend 10 days apart from you or 20 days without saying something complimentary or lovey dovey) Then you will kill them, fuzzily blank out on why and what happened and move them to the past, the next powerful person is 'your man/woman\" then."
        ],
        [
          "2. You distrust people often without even knowing them, you always carry a coin and flip it when you meet people, Cavendish gave you this coin and told you Lady Luck will guide you on who is good, who is bad, who has it in for you (mechanically you flip on every person you meet, win you like them/no threat unless they attack physically, loss you test again.  Win on second they are blah, you dont care, loss on second you do not trust them and will watch them constantly expecting an attack, yelling, beating, etc.)"
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Franklin Bishop III",
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1926.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "Chapman, IL"
        ],
        [
          "Fortune Telling"
        ],
        [
          "The EYE lets you pierce the veil between reality and potential realities, you can use runes, cards, palm reading, tea leaves etc.  You can extend this power to them to let them see through and even potentially interact with other places.  For the price of one temp WP they can see wraiths OR Spirits for one hour, for the price of one temp WP they can talk to them.  For the price of one permanent WP they can see wraiths OR spirits for a year and a day, for the price of one permanent WP they can talk to wraiths OR spirits for a year and a day.For the Price of two permanent WP they can make themselves invisible to wraiths or spirits for a year and a day. For the Price of three permannent WP they can detect when someone is under the effect of a power (vampire or not) and if they have the appropriate knowledge or lore, what it is.  The expenditure of WP is completely voluntary and may not be forced in any way.  Each point of WP that is used causes one Thorn. If anyone gets more than three thorns you must warn them out of character that they are feeling lethargic and their beast is getting restless and they should stop."
        ],
        [],
        [],
        [],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals"
        ],
        [
          "Bring Paul back to the circus, he is a key tool for Barouqe (your master and lover) to ascend to the infernal trinity"
        ],
